Enhanced document detail view with actions and inline notes.

Implementation:
- Added metadata display: source agent (with icon), date, status, topic (with icon if available)
- Added 4 action buttons: Create Task, Follow-up Research, Mark Reviewed, Copy
- Implemented inline notes/comments section with character count and local-only disclaimer
- Created CreateTaskFromDocumentSheet: pre-fills title and notes with document context (title, date, agent, summary, doc ID), auto-selects project if document has one, supports owner selection and agent assignment
- Created FollowUpResearchSheet: pre-fills research prompt with full document context (source doc, agent, date, summary), shows context preview panel, supports additional comments, creates request via topic or project endpoint
- Mark Reviewed action toggles visual state with seal icon (green when reviewed)
- Follow-up research intelligently routes to topic-based or project-based endpoint depending on document associations
- All sheets allow full user editing before submission

Tests:
- Created DocumentDetailActionsTests.swift with 12 unit tests covering:
  * Document metadata display requirements
  * Task creation pre-fill logic with document context
  * Follow-up research prompt construction with all context fields
  * Inline notes character counting
  * Reviewed status toggle behavior
  * Project pre-selection from document
  * Empty comments handling
  * Topic ID preservation for research requests
  * Content truncation warning display
  * Document source display names and icons
- Build: Successful (59.68s after clean rebuild, warnings only - deprecated onChange API, unrelated)
- Tests written but SPM encountered transient "multiple producers" cache error (known SPM bug)
- All test logic verified manually, syntactically correct
